api/backend.title: Backend REST API
api/backend.description: The Semantest Backend API provides RESTful endpoints for managing image downloads, sessions, and automation workflows. It complements the WebSocket server by offering traditional HTTP-based interactions.

api/client.title: Client SDK API
api/client.description: The Semantest Client SDK provides a TypeScript/JavaScript interface for automating web interactions through semantic commands.

architecture/introduction.title: Architecture Introduction
architecture/introduction.description: Semantest is built on a foundation of modern software architecture principles, combining Domain-Driven Design (DDD), Event-Driven Architecture (EDA), and microservices patterns to create a robust, scalable, and maintainable testing framework.

components/browser/websocket.title: WebSocket Server
components/browser/websocket.description: The Semantest WebSocket Server is the central communication hub that orchestrates all automation activities. It provides real-time, bidirectional communication between clients and browser extensions.

components/core/overview.title: Core Components Overview
components/core/overview.description: The Semantest Core package provides fundamental building blocks and shared utilities used across all components of the system. It implements the foundational patterns and abstractions that ensure consistency and maintainability.

components/domains/image-download.title: Image Download Domain
components/domains/image-download.description: The Image Download domain encapsulates all business logic related to discovering, selecting, and downloading images from web sources. It implements Domain-Driven Design principles to provide a clean, maintainable solution for semantic image acquisition.

components/extensions/chrome.title: Chrome Extension
components/extensions/chrome.description: The Semantest Chrome Extension is the core component that enables browser automation through semantic commands. It acts as the bridge between your automation scripts and the web pages you want to interact with.

components/sdk/client.title: Client SDK
components/sdk/client.description: The Semantest Client SDK provides a comprehensive TypeScript/JavaScript interface for automating web interactions through semantic commands. It enables developers to integrate Semantest's powerful automation capabilities into their applications.

deployment/docker.title: Docker Deployment
deployment/docker.description: Deploy Semantest using Docker for consistent, reproducible environments across development, staging, and production.

developer-guide/best-practices.title: Best Practices
developer-guide/best-practices.description: This guide outlines best practices for developing, maintaining, and deploying Semantest components. Following these practices ensures code quality, performance, and maintainability.

developer-guide/contributing.title: Contributing to Semantest
developer-guide/contributing.description: Thank you for your interest in contributing to Semantest! This guide will help you get started with contributing to our semantic web automation framework.

developer-guide/debugging.title: Debugging Guide
developer-guide/debugging.description: This guide provides comprehensive debugging strategies and tools for troubleshooting issues across all Semantest components.

developer-guide/style-guide.title: Code Style Guide
developer-guide/style-guide.description: This guide defines the coding standards and conventions used throughout the Semantest project. Consistent code style improves readability, maintainability, and collaboration.

developer-guide/testing.title: Testing Guide
developer-guide/testing.description: This guide covers testing practices, patterns, and tools used in the Semantest project. We follow Test-Driven Development (TDD) principles and maintain high test coverage standards.

getting-started/getting-started.title: Getting Started with Semantest - A Developer's Journey
getting-started/getting-started.description: Write browser tests like you'd explain them to a colleague. Learn how Semantest transforms frustrating test automation into intuitive, AI-powered testing.

getting-started/quick-start.title: Quick Start
getting-started/quick-start.description: Get up and running with Semantest in just 5 minutes! This guide will walk you through installation, basic setup, and your first automation.

success-stories/success-stories.title: Semantest Success Stories - Real Teams, Real Results
success-stories/success-stories.description: Discover how teams transformed their testing from maintenance nightmares to productive automation with Semantest.

tutorials/amazon-shopping.title: Real-World Tutorial - Testing Amazon's Shopping Flow
tutorials/amazon-shopping.description: Learn Semantest by testing one of the web's most complex UIs - Amazon's shopping flow. A practical, hands-on tutorial.
